name: Pinoy Hatdog
text:
Some thoughts/suggestions:
- Go to the BIOS, set everything back to factory defaults.
- Check if your PC has any soft OCing software (e.g. Asus has it's own soft OCing program that by default auto OCs your CPU). If there's one, turn it off.
- Check if there's enough airflow in and out of your case. Clean the airflow points of your case to ensure the air can go in and out easily.
- Maybe the temps are high, but are still within the acceptable bounds of the chip?
- Check if your CPU's heatsink got dislodged somehow (highly unlikely).
- Replace your CPU's thermal paste.
